<TITLE> 12 pro-nationalist parties support BNP </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 6 (bdnews24.com)  Twelve pro-nationalist political parties have thrown their weight behind the BNP's seven-point charter of demands including rescheduling the election with time extension for the submission of nomination. The BNP chairperson met the leaders of the 12 pro-nationalist parties on Thursday evening at her political office at Gulshan in the city, BNP secretary general Khandker Delwar Hossain said on Thursday. "The country is passing through a critical time," he said, adding the leaders of the parties asked the authorities to meet the demands if they were to facilitate a credible and free election. "They have also urged the authorities to extend time for nomination." Besides Delwar, joint secretary general Nazrul Islam Khan and office secretary Rizvi Ahmed were also present at the meeting. Shafiul Alam Prodhan and Khandaker Lutfur Rahman of National Democratic Party, Sheikh Shawkat Hossain Nilu and Farhad Hossain of National People's Party, Saifuddin Ahmed Moni of Democratic League Abdul Mobin of Islamic Party, Najimuddin Al-Asad of Bangladesh Liberal Democratic Party, Sheikh Anwarul Huq and Altaf Hossain Munna of National Awami Party, Fazlur Rahman of Nirdoliyo Jono Andolon, A N M Yusuf and Abul Khair of Muslim League (Yusuf), Mohammed Kamruzzaman and Atikul Islam of Muslim League (Kamruzzaman), Sekandar Ali Moni and M Akhter Hossain of Bangladesh Labour Party, Shamsul Huda Mamun and Mustafizur Rahman Iran of Bangladesh Labour Party (Huda), Khandaker Golam Mortuza and Alamgir Mazumdar of National Democratic Party and Bidhur Kanti Biswas of Hindu League represented the 12 parties in the meeting. bdne
